past couple of years.

00:01:06.110 --> 00:01:08.680
But with that, I'd like
to turn things over

00:01:08.680 --> 00:01:12.450
to Mark Levinson, who's
the director of this movie,

00:01:12.450 --> 00:01:16.550
to introduce the
other panelists.

00:01:16.550 --> 00:01:20.350
MARK LEVINSON: So just I'll give
a little bit of an introduction

00:01:20.350 --> 00:01:21.970
to what's going on here.

00:01:21.970 --> 00:01:24.260
I don't know how many
people know about this film.

00:01:24.260 --> 00:01:27.390
We've been working
on it for years.

00:01:27.390 --> 00:01:32.280
David Kaplan first had an idea
to do something like this.

00:01:32.280 --> 00:01:35.664
He is a theorist, and
saw that something

00:01:35.664 --> 00:01:37.580
was happening that was
going to be monumental.

00:01:37.580 --> 00:01:42.130
And was a unique situation
in the history of science,

00:01:42.130 --> 00:01:43.790
where something was
going to turn on.

00:01:43.790 --> 00:01:45.665
Do you want to just get
a little intro, Dave,

00:01:45.665 --> 00:01:46.730
before Savas gets back?

00:01:49.252 --> 00:01:50.085
DAVID KAPLAN: Hello.

00:01:52.780 --> 00:01:56.500
About in 2006, I
did a calculation

00:01:56.500 --> 00:01:58.720
that any theorist
could do and discovered

00:01:58.720 --> 00:02:01.600
that somebody needed to
make a documentary film.

00:02:01.600 --> 00:02:04.630
And I was the only
one in my field

00:02:04.630 --> 00:02:06.530
willing to do
something like that.

00:02:06.530 --> 00:02:07.620
And so I started.

00:02:07.620 --> 00:02:11.039
I bought a camera, I
started doing interviews,

00:02:11.039 --> 00:02:13.780
and discovered I didn't know
how to operate a camera.

00:02:13.780 --> 00:02:17.940
And then had to figure out how
this film was going to be made.

00:02:17.940 --> 00:02:19.890
I didn't really have a
desire to make a movie,

00:02:19.890 --> 00:02:22.070
I had a desire for
this movie to be made.

00:02:22.070 --> 00:02:24.550
But I understood it had
to be made from somebody

00:02:24.550 --> 00:02:28.841
who was deep inside the
world, and sort of living it.

00:02:28.841 --> 00:02:31.340
Somebody who was not going to
be intimidated by the physics,

00:02:31.340 --> 00:02:34.290
but understood that
this was a human drama

00:02:34.290 --> 00:02:37.470
and that this is a side of
science that I never see

00:02:37.470 --> 00:02:38.800
captured in any other way.

00:02:38.800 --> 00:02:39.841
So I wanted to see it.

00:02:39.841 --> 00:02:40.840
And I wanted to feel it.

00:02:40.840 --> 00:02:43.450
And I wanted my
friends to be known,

00:02:43.450 --> 00:02:47.006
because these are my favorite
people in the universe.

00:02:47.006 --> 00:02:48.380
I didn't understand
why everybody

00:02:48.380 --> 00:02:49.650
didn't know about them.

00:02:49.650 --> 00:02:52.610
And I didn't understand why
this amazing event was going

00:02:52.610 --> 00:02:55.210
to happen and nobody was
going to know about it.

00:02:55.210 --> 00:02:56.960
I ended up being
wrong about that.

00:02:56.960 --> 00:02:58.300
It was all over the papers.

00:02:58.300 --> 00:03:01.410
But that was the
original motivation.

00:03:01.410 --> 00:03:03.690
And then mark discovered
some crazy physicist

00:03:03.690 --> 00:03:05.360
wanted to make a movie.

00:03:05.360 --> 00:03:08.370
And Mark's training is a
PhD in particle theory,

00:03:08.370 --> 00:03:10.290
and then went on to
make movies, which

00:03:10.290 --> 00:03:11.415
is the natural progression.

00:03:15.420 --> 00:03:18.020
He is the only one in
that Hollywood gang

00:03:18.020 --> 00:03:19.742
who would really
understand immediately

00:03:19.742 --> 00:03:21.450
that there was an
incredible story there.

00:03:21.450 --> 00:03:25.880
That the humans that are doing
it are amazing and interesting,

00:03:25.880 --> 00:03:28.760
and that you can create
something dramatic out

00:03:28.760 --> 00:03:32.790
of something that sounds
incredibly technical.

00:03:32.790 --> 00:03:35.290
MARK LEVINSON: And here
we are many years later,

00:03:35.290 --> 00:03:38.280
with an incredible cast.

00:03:38.280 --> 00:03:41.560
And so actually, I'm going to
roll, as just an introduction,

00:03:41.560 --> 00:03:44.470
we have the trailer
that we have released.

00:03:44.470 --> 00:03:49.750
