00:28:14.976 --> 00:28:21.385
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:29:00.953 --> 00:29:06.250
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:29:06.250 --> 00:29:12.010
MARK LEVINSON: So what is
the role, for you, in music?

00:29:12.010 --> 00:29:14.070
And do you think there
is an overlap between art

00:29:14.070 --> 00:29:14.400
and science?

00:29:14.400 --> 00:29:16.358
Do you think artists can
learn from scientists?

00:29:16.358 --> 00:29:18.762
Do you think scientists
can learn from artists?

00:29:18.762 --> 00:29:20.803
FABIOLA GIANOTTI: I don't
want to speak too much,

00:29:20.803 --> 00:29:25.920
but for me music is a very
important component of my life.

00:29:25.920 --> 00:29:30.860
I think I am a
modestly good physicist

00:29:30.860 --> 00:29:33.350
because I've been
studying music.

00:29:33.350 --> 00:29:36.600
And music and physics are
really very close to each other.

00:29:36.600 --> 00:29:40.780
They both require
rules, mathematics.

00:29:40.780 --> 00:29:45.750
Music is based on a harmony,
which is the physics of sounds,

00:29:45.750 --> 00:29:46.700
essentially.

00:29:46.700 --> 00:29:49.090
And a Bach cantata,
for instance,

00:29:49.090 --> 00:29:50.830
is a piece of mathematics.

00:29:50.830 --> 00:29:52.690
Because Bach was really
following the rules

00:29:52.690 --> 00:29:54.230
in a very strict way.

00:29:54.230 --> 00:29:57.200
On top of which, Bach
has put all of his heart.

00:29:57.200 --> 00:30:00.250
So music is rules, and
a lot of creativity,

00:30:00.250 --> 00:30:02.190
and fantasy, as much as physics.

00:30:02.190 --> 00:30:05.170
So for me, hey are really
two different expressions

00:30:05.170 --> 00:30:08.870
of the same human [INAUDIBLE].

00:30:08.870 --> 00:30:13.880
SAVAS DIMOPOULOS: Well, I was
the last child in a family,

00:30:13.880 --> 00:30:15.500
so my parents were
sick and tired

00:30:15.500 --> 00:30:18.250
of teaching music to their
kids by that time I was born.

00:30:18.250 --> 00:30:20.650
So unfortunately, even
though I love music,

00:30:20.650 --> 00:30:22.490
I don't play an instrument.

00:30:22.490 --> 00:30:26.920
On the other hand,
