00:47:47.484 --> 00:47:48.900
NIMA ARKANI-HAMED:
But we've known

00:47:48.900 --> 00:47:52.100
something is going on
at roughly these energy

00:47:52.100 --> 00:47:56.190
scales, or distance scales,
depending on how you count,

00:47:56.190 --> 00:47:58.400
since 1895.

00:47:58.400 --> 00:48:03.950
So in 1895, people
discovered radioactivity.

00:48:03.950 --> 00:48:06.820
And you think about it, this
is a completely insane thing.

00:48:06.820 --> 00:48:08.900
You have a nucleus
that's sitting there--

00:48:08.900 --> 00:48:09.960
or let's make it simple.

00:48:09.960 --> 00:48:10.980
You have a neutron.

00:48:10.980 --> 00:48:12.430
Take a neutron an empty space.

00:48:12.430 --> 00:48:14.320
It sits there for
15 minutes and then

00:48:14.320 --> 00:48:16.670
it disintegrates into
a proton, an electron,

00:48:16.670 --> 00:48:18.920
and something called an
antielectron neutrino.

00:48:18.920 --> 00:48:23.090
But anyway, 15 minutes is a
gargantuan, long, long, long,

00:48:23.090 --> 00:48:27.040
long time scale compared to all
the time and distance scales

00:48:27.040 --> 00:48:28.720
of atomic and nuclear physics.

00:48:28.720 --> 00:48:33.140
And we now understand
why it takes

00:48:33.140 --> 00:48:34.750
so long is because
the physics that's

00:48:34.750 --> 00:48:38.440
ultimately responsible for
making the neutron disintegrate

00:48:38.440 --> 00:48:40.890
operates at distances there
are, in turn, 100 times

00:48:40.890 --> 00:48:43.880
smaller than the nucleus itself.

00:48:43.880 --> 00:48:50.850
And so people indirectly
knew about this scale,

00:48:50.850 --> 00:48:52.800
as I said, even in 1895.

00:48:52.800 --> 00:48:54.320
But we properly
understood the way

00:48:54.320 --> 00:48:57.060
to conceptualize it already
by the '50s and '60s.

00:48:57.060 --> 00:48:59.090
And it wasn't until the
1980s that we actually

00:48:59.090 --> 00:49:01.220
discovered the particles
responsible directly

00:49:01.220 --> 00:49:02.640
for radioactivity.

00:49:02.640 --> 00:49:06.280
And then the fact that it's
another 20, 25 years after that

00:49:06.280 --> 00:49:11.620
before we go another factor
of 1 and 1/2 higher in energy.

00:49:11.620 --> 00:49:14.534
Had the Higgs been down
there just a factor of two

00:49:14.534 --> 00:49:15.950
lighter than it
was, it would have

00:49:15.950 --> 00:49:18.870
been discovered in the 1980s.

00:49:18.870 --> 00:49:21.960
But this is a
difficult business.

00:49:21.960 --> 00:49:28.670
